Language AI — Backend API
 1.0.0
OAS 3.1
/openapi.json
Backend service for the Language AI stuttering practice app.

Authentication
Most endpoints require a Bearer token. Call POST /auth/login to get one, then click Authorize (top-right) and paste the token.

Roles
Role    Can do
PATIENT    Play the game, take proficiency tests, analyse audio
DOCTOR    Everything above + manage phrases and read all users
Contact Rahul Bhatt

Authorize
auth
Sign up, log in, and inspect the current session. Login returns a Bearer token — pass it as Authorization: Bearer <token> on all protected endpoints.



POST
/auth/signup
Create a new account


POST
/auth/login
Log in and get a Bearer token


GET
/auth/me
Get the current user


users
Read, update, and delete user accounts. A user can always act on their own account; doctors may act on any account.



GET
/users
List all users



GET
/users/{user_id}
Get a user by ID



PATCH
/users/{user_id}
Update a user



DELETE
/users/{user_id}
Delete a user


phrases
Manage practice sentences (disfluency phrases). Creating, editing, and deleting phrases is restricted to doctors.



POST
/phrases
Create a practice phrase



GET
/phrases
List practice phrases



GET
/phrases/{phrase_id}
Get a phrase by ID



PATCH
/phrases/{phrase_id}
Update a phrase



DELETE
/phrases/{phrase_id}
Delete a phrase


game
Patient-facing game endpoints. Returns a randomised batch of unseen phrases for the current difficulty level and records that they were shown.



GET
/game/phrases
Get game phrases for this session



GET
/game/targeted-phrases
Get a personalised, adaptive batch of practice phrases


proficiency
Proficiency test flow: start a 40-phrase assessment, then submit answers to receive an assigned starting difficulty.



POST
/proficiency-test/start
Start Test



POST
/proficiency-test/{test_id}/submit
Submit Test


audio
Audio analysis pipeline. Upload a WAV/MP3 recording and receive a full disfluency breakdown, fluency score, coverage score, and retry flag.



GET
/v1/audio/defaults
Get Defaults


POST
/v1/audio/analyze
Analyse a recording (stateless, no DB)


GET
/v1/audio/patients/{user_id}/practice-skill
Get a patient's per-sound practice mastery matrix


conversation
Conversational AI sessions. Start a session, submit audio turns, and receive AI-generated replies with synthesised voice. Doctors can retrieve full session transcripts.



POST
/v1/conversation/session/start
Start a new conversation session (Ollie greets first)



POST
/v1/conversation/session/{session_id}/reply
Submit child audio and get the AI reply



POST
/v1/conversation/session/{session_id}/end
End a conversation session and get a disfluency breakdown



GET
/v1/conversation/session
List all sessions for the current patient



GET
/v1/conversation/session/{session_id}
Get full turn-by-turn session report



GET
/v1/conversation/patients/{user_id}/progress
Get disfluency trend across all sessions for a patient



GET
/v1/conversation/patients/{user_id}/disfluency-profile
Get a patient's disfluency profile (top problem sounds / types / words)


admin
Runtime configuration management. Doctor role required. Read and update business rules (phrase cooldown days, test size, etc.) without a code deploy.



GET
/v1/admin/config
List all runtime configuration entries



GET
/v1/admin/config/{key}
Get a single config entry by key



PUT
/v1/admin/config/{key}
Update a config value


repeat-after-me


GET
/v1/repeat-after-me/start
Start the game — the AI's spoken introduction (by name)



GET
/v1/repeat-after-me/next-phrase
Get the next phrase to practise (with AI-voiced audio)



POST
/v1/repeat-after-me/attempt
Analyse a practice attempt and store the result


health


GET
/health
Health check


